- 'Within the past week' is a time constraint for the status updates.

- "success rate" is calculated as the ratio of successful commands to the total commands;
- "error-free success rate" is calculated as the ratio of successful commands to the total commands excluding errors;
- "failed commands" are the commands that did not succeed and are calculated as the difference between total commands and successful commands.

- "Command execution" refers to the process of executing a command on a vehicle or device;
